<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Rail informationRail Users may travel to nearby Layton or Blackpool North Stations, both of which are main line stations operating regular services around the North West. For more information about rail travel please contact National Rail Enquiries on 08457 484950 or visit www.nationalrail.co.uk.<br/><br/>Local directionThe Hospital is situated on Whinney Heys Road, immediately next to Blackpool Zoo in the Layton area of Blackpool.<br/>Travellers by car should head from the A583 Preston New Road, onto South Park Drive, which becomes East Park Drive, past Stanley Park and the Zoo and turn right into Whinpark Avenue, which is the northern boundary of the Hospital.<br/>Rail Users may travel to nearby Layton or Blackpool North Stations, both of which are main line stations operating regular services around the North West.<br/><br/><br/>Road informationTravellers by car should head from the A583 Preston New Road, onto South Park Drive, which becomes East Park Drive, past Stanley Park and the Zoo and upto Four Lane Ends roundabout. Take the fourth exit at the roundabout and turn right into Whinney Heys Road.<br/><br/>Bus informationThe hospital is well served by regular bus services to and from Blackpool.<br/>For timetable information about Bus Services across the Fylde Coast, please call 01253 473000 


